headline: The Bull Case For Fastenal (FAST) Could Change Following Dividend Hike And CEO Transition Timing
summary: Fastenal Company’s board previously declared a US$0.24 per-share cash dividend, payable on February 26, 2026, to shareholders of record as of January 29, 2026, following a 9.1% increase in its quarterly payout. This higher dividend, announced alongside an approaching CEO transition and upcoming Q4 2025 earnings release, highlights how capital returns, leadership change, and operating conditions are converging for the industrial distributor.
